snippet.title: Master System Longplay [249] Psycho Fox (US)
snippet.description:
http://www.longplays.org

Played by: KAGE-008

Psycho Fox is a video game published by Sega for the Master System in 1989. In Brazil, Tectoy released the game as Sapo Xule: Os Invasores do Brejo (translated as "Xule Frog: Invaders of the Swamp" ), in which Psycho Fox and his friends were replaced by Sapo Xule (a Brazilian comic frog character), a pig, a turtle and a mouse.

One thing to note is that the game features secret warps as well. Since the purpose here is to show it in its entirety, this is a warpless playthrough.
